# {{SLUG}} — Resolver

Canonical router for this workspace. `AGENTS.md` and `.claude/CLAUDE.md` are
entrypoints; this file decides which skill or rule to load. Read the target
before acting. If two routes match, read both and use the more specific one.
Gates always apply.

Sections outside the `resolver-gen` markers are yours — the toolkit never
touches them. The block inside the markers is regenerated from skill
frontmatter by `gen-catalog.mjs` (`aios update` refreshes skills; re-run the
catalog after adding your own).

## Always-On Gates

| Trigger | Load |
|---|---|
| Any git operation | `.claude/rules/git-workflow.md` — this is a personal workspace: work on **master only**, no branches/worktrees/PRs, commit when the owner asks. (The AIOS *product* repos have the opposite rule — toolkit work happens there, in worktrees) |
| Any access/tier/sharing question, or content missing access frontmatter | `.claude/rules/frontmatter.md` — default-deny: untagged content never syncs; **private→admin** never leaves this machine |
| A `6-business/` question (business-owner context) | `.claude/rules/access-control.md` — path-level exclusion from `sync_include`, a second layer beyond `access:` tags |
| Anything about to leave the workspace (push, share, promote) | `.claude/rules/publishing.md` — promotion is deliberate; nothing leaves until `aios push` |
| A decision made in any session | `.claude/rules/decision-log.md` — one row per decision, logged when made |
| Time/hours logging | `.claude/rules/hours.md` — hours-log (human) vs time-log (agent runtime) are separate lanes |
| Any UI work in this workspace | `.claude/rules/design-system.md` — use **@aios-alpha/design** tokens, never ad-hoc palettes |
| Cross-document links or navigation | `.claude/rules/interlinking.md` — path-relative links; each directory's **index.md** is the entry point |
| A toolkit bug or product improvement surfaces | Dogfood here, ship there: write the finding here; implement + PR in the **aios-workspace** product repo (`.claude/rules/git-workflow.md`) |

